author: CNN
description: Grammy-winning artist Lil Nas X has been arrested for battery of a police officer. He was found early Thursday morning in Studio City on Ventura Boulevard and charged at officers, according to a public information officer with the LAPD.
title: Lil Nas X arrested for battery of a police officer

author: CNN
description: Israel has given final approval to expand a massive settlement project known as E1, that will effectively slice the occupied West Bank in half. It's been widely condemned by countries such as Britain, Canada and France, calling it a "flagrant violation of international law" and an end to the idea of a Palestinian state. Israeli settlements in the West Bank are considered illegal under international law. CNN’s Nic Robertson visits Palestinian communities who would be forcibly displaced by the plan and explains why it is so controversial.
title: Israel approves plan to 'erase' Palestinian state

author: CNN
description: French streamer Jean Pormanove, real name Raphaël Graven, died during a nearly 12-day streaming challenge. Before this livestream, he regularly endured shocking scenes of alleged humiliation and abuse at the hands of fellow streamers, whose lawyers claim the incidents were scripted or consented to.
title: French Streamer dies during online extreme challenge

author: CNN
description: As the earliest stages of a massive assault on Gaza City take shape, Israel is calling up tens of thousands of reservists to take part in the impending military operation. Israel is planning to bring in 60,000 more reserve troops and extend the service of another 20,000 as UN fears the outcome can lead to more death and destruction. CNN's Oren Liebermann reports. #cnn #news #world #politics
title: Israel plans on massive assault on Gaza City

author: CNN
description: A new study found the world's largest carnivorous bat is more social than previously thought. Commonly known as greater false vampire bats, this rare species was observed hunting and playing together and even appeared to hug family members as a form of greeting. #cnn #science #bats #hug
title: Spectral bats form 'cuddle balls' and like to hug

author: CNN
description: 75-year-old Donna Adelson is facing murder charges in the death of her former son-in-law, Florida State University law professor Dan Markel, who was killed by two hit men in 2014. CNN's Jean Casarez reports on the details that led to Adelson's arrest and trial, where she is accused of being the mastermind behind the murder-for-hire plot.
title: This 75-year-old is on trial for a 2014 murder. The victim was her son-in-law

author: CNN
description: After this week’s diplomatic dance between world leaders over the Russia-Ukraine war, the world has been eagerly waiting for the announcement of a face-to-face summit with Russian President Vladimir Putin and Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky. While the meeting has not been confirmed yet, the possibility of peace talks has revived memories of three key moments in 20th century diplomatic history. CNN’s Nathan Hodge explains. #CNN #News
title: Three parallels from history ahead of possible Ukraine peace talks

author: CNN
description: 25 of 28 Major U.S cities are sinking, and Houston is sinking the fastest. CNN's Boris Sanchez explains this groundbreaking problem and how subsidence is quietly reshaping the ground we live on.
title: Houston, we have a sinking problem

author: CNN
description: Emmy-nominated actress Patricia Arquette chats with CNN's Elizabeth Wagmeister about what she knows about season three of 'Severance.' #cnn #cnnnews #emmys
title: Patricia Arquette talks season 3 of ‘Severance’

author: CNN
description: Texas Republicans are poised to pass a new congressional map backed by President Donald Trump that will create five more GOP-leaning House districts in time for next year’s midterm elections. CNN's Arlette Saenz reports from Austin about how Gov. Gavin Newsom is vowing to fight back.
title: Democrats vow to fight back against GOP redistricting

author: CNN
description:
A New York appeals court has thrown out the roughly half-billion dollar judgment against President Donald Trump in the civil fraud case brought by the state’s attorney general. CNN's Elie Honig reports.

#cnn #news #trump #newyork
title: NY appeals court voids nearly $500m penalty against Trump

author: CNN
description: A 28-year-old man was arrested on Wednesday after setting fire to a check in counter at Milan’s Malpensa Airport, causing significant damage and injuring at least one person, police say. The man was tackled by airport police, and is facing charges of aggravated damage to public property.
title: Panic in Milan airport as man sets fire to check-in desk

author: CNN
description: According to Ukrainian authorities, Russia launched its largest drone and missile attack on Ukraine in more than a month. The attack comes just days after US President Donald Trump met with Russian leader Vladimir Putin, followed by a summit with Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky and European leaders. #CNN #news
title: Russia launches largest drone and missile attack in more than a month

author: CNN
description: Patricia Arquette talks to CNN’s Elizabeth Wagmeister about Apple TV’s “Severance” dominating the 2025 Emmy awards with 27 nominations, plus teases what’s ahead for Season 3. #CNN #News
title: Patricia Arquette teases 'Severance' Season 3: 'It will be some time'

author: CNN
description: One reservist tells CNN's Oren Liebermann he won’t return after more than 300 days deployed in Gaza. A new study shows about 40% of reservists feel less motivated to serve, and Israel’s top general warns of burnout as the military prepares to call up 60,000 more troops for a prolonged Gaza City offensive.
title: Israeli reservists are burning out

author: CNN
description: Fugitive Thomas Callam Phillips vanished into the remote forests of New Zealand’s North Island in 2021 with his three children—now 12-, 10-, and 9-years-old— sparking a four-year search that has gripped the country. Now, after years of silence, his family is making a heartfelt public appeal: they miss him and their grandchildren—and they’re urging him to come home.
title: Fugitive father and kids living in wilderness

author: CNN
description: On Wednesday, several parents of children who died at Camp Mystic after a catastrophic flood on July 4 sat before a Texas state Senate committee and called for stronger safety standards at youth camps in Texas. #cnn #news
title: Parents of girls lost in Texas flooding criticize safety measures

author: CNN
description: As Erin makes its closest approach to the coast, it remains a Category 2 hurricane. According to the National Hurricane Center at 5 a.m. on Thursday, Erin was just over 200 miles east-southeast from Cape Hatteras, North Carolina and has begun to move away from the coast. #CNN #news
title: Erin remains Category 2 hurricane

author: CNN
description:
Audie sits down with The Atlantic staff writer Faith Hill, who covers what she's described as "the slow, quiet demise of American romance," for a breakdown of the uniquely modern challenges and consequences of searching for love on your phone.

Listen to the full episode of CNN's The Assignment podcast: https://link.chtbl.com/Sq6SgL_j

#CNN #News #Dating
title: Dating apps and the demise of American romance | The Assignment

author: CNN
description: Ahead of a massive military parade to mark the 80th anniversary of the end of WWII, the Chinese government invited foreign media to a practice session on the outskirts of Beijing. CNN Beijing Bureau Chief Steven Jiang reports from heavily guarded barracks and discusses what the event means for the world's biggest standing army under leader Xi Jinping. #CNN #News #China
title: Chinese troops train for massive parade

author: CNN
description: CNN's Anderson Cooper speaks with Jeffrey Epstein accuser Virginia Giuffre's brother and sister-in-law about their sister's fight for justice.
title: Virginia Giuffre's family becomes emotional recalling her fight for justice

author: CNN
description: As Vice President JD Vance staged a lunch to thank the National Guard members that President Donald Trump deployed to Washington, DC, he was met with loud protesters at Union Station. #CNN #News
title: Protesters boo Vance and Hegseth during National Guard visit

author: CNN
description: Target CEO Brian Cornell is stepping down after 11 years, as the company faces slumping sales and backlash to its DEI rollback. Here's what happened to Target. #CNN #news #target
title: What happened to Target?

author: CNN
description: Two brothers from Mexico were arrested by federal agents on Friday in Norwalk, Connecticut. Video shows two officers aggressively tugging Leonel Chavez’s arm while he sits inside a car before saying he is under arrest. A second video filmed by a passerby shows Chavez's brother, Ricardo, running away from an agent before getting tased, prompting him to suddenly collapse on the ground. The DHS told CNN in a statement that ICE agents were operating in Norwalk last week, but they did not specify whether it was ICE officers who arrested the Chavez brothers.
title: Mexican brothers arrested, one tased by federal agents

author: CNN
description: CNN’s Anderson Cooper speaks with Jeffrey Epstein accuser Virginia Giuffre’s brother and sister-in-law about Ghislaine Maxwell’s prison transfer and their sister’s fight for justice. #CNN #News
title: 'Insult to survivors': Virginia Giuffre's family reacts to Ghislaine Maxwell's prison transfer

author: CNN
description: A federal judge said he would not unseal grand jury transcripts and exhibits from the investigation into Jeffrey Epstein – rejecting the Justice Department’s request to make them public. #CNN #News
title: 'Diversion': Judge blasts Trump team's bid to unseal Epstein docs

author: CNN
description: Judge Frank Caprio has died at the age of 88 after a battle with pancreatic cancer, according to a post on his Instagram page. Caprio is known for starring on the reality TV series "Caught in Providence" and for spreading kindness on social media.
title: ‘The Nicest Judge in the World’ dies at 88
